This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with video caching, which is a basic network functionality. Additionally, the paper proposes a learning-aided approach to improve caching replacement algorithms, which is a common problem in network architecture. 

The paper also uses deep neural networks (DNNs) for prediction, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). 

Furthermore, the paper's focus on adapting to constantly changing popularity suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). 

The paper's use of real-world datasets and experiments suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Multimedia (cs.MM). 

Finally, the paper's focus on addressing limitations in caching replacement algorithms suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), as caching can be used to improve security and privacy in network architectures.
